Ingredients
1 head cauliflower
2 Tbs coconut or olive oil
sea salt, 
garlic, 
ginger, 
coconut aminos, 
freshly ground black pepper

Instructions
Place the cauliflower into a food processor and pulse until it has a grainy rice-like consistency. 
Season with sea salt and freshly ground black pepper.
Meanwhile, heat a large sauté pan over medium-high heat. 
Add coconut or olive oil when hot.
Sauté cauliflower in a pan with oil and any 
seasonings desired (sea salt, garlic, ginger, coconut aminos, curry, or just freshly ground black pepper).